CFrame: Contains information regarding the Part's position and a matrix that defines the Part's rotation. Can read/write. [More info](https://developer.roblox.com/en-us/api-reference/property/BasePart/CFrame)
CameraMode: An enum that describes how a Player's camera is allowed to behave. [More info](https://developer.roblox.com/en-us/api-reference/enum/CameraMode).
CameraType: Defines how the camera will behave. [More info](https://developer.roblox.com/en-us/api-reference/enum/CameraType)
CycleOffset: Controls how the decals are positioned along the wire. [More info](http://wiki.roblox.com/index.php/CycleOffset)
DataReady: Read-only. If true, this Player's persistent data can be loaded, false otherwise. [Info on Data Persistence](http://wiki.roblox.com/index.php/ROBLOX_Scripting_How_To:_Data_Persistence).
ExplosionType: Defines the behavior of the Explosion. [More info](https://developer.roblox.com/en-us/api-reference/property/Explosion/ExplosionType)
Face: Describes the face of the Part the decal will be applied to. [More info](https://developer.roblox.com/en-us/api-reference/enum/NormalId)
FloorWire: Renders a thin cylinder than can be adorned with textures that 'flow' from one object to the next. Has basic pathing abilities and attempts to to not intersect anything. [More info](http://wiki.roblox.com/index.php/FloorWire_Guide)
GeographicLatitude: The latitude position the level is placed at. This affects sun position. [More info](https://developer.roblox.com/en-us/api-reference/property/Lighting/GeographicLatitude)
GetBaseSets: Returns a table containing a list of the various setIds that are ROBLOX approved. [More info on sets](http://wiki.roblox.com/index.php/Sets)
GetCollection: Returns a table for the assets stored in the category. A category is an setId from www.roblox.com that links to a set. [More info on table format](http://wiki.roblox.com/index.php?title=API:Class/InsertService/GetCollection). [More info on sets](http://wiki.roblox.com/index.php/Sets)
GetUserSets: Returns a table containing a list of the various setIds that correspond to argument 'userId'. [More info on sets](http://wiki.roblox.com/index.php/Sets)
Icon: The current Texture of the Mouse Icon. Stored as a string, for more information on how to format the string [go here](http://wiki.roblox.com/index.php/Content)
Image: Specifies the asset id of the texture to display. [More info](https://developer.roblox.com/en-us/api-reference/property/ImageButton/Image)
IsA: Returns a boolean if this Instance is of type 'className' or a is a subclass of type 'className'. If 'className' is not a valid class type in ROBLOX, this function will always return false. [More info](https://developer.roblox.com/en-us/api-reference/function/Instance/IsA)
LoadAsset: Returns a Model containing the Instance that resides at AssetId on the web. This call will also yield the script until the model is returned. Script execution can still continue, however, if you use a [coroutine](https://developer.roblox.com/en-us/api-reference/lua-docs/coroutine).
MakeJoints: Creates the appropriate SurfaceJoints with all parts that are touching this Instance (including internal joints in the Instance, as in a Model). This uses the SurfaceTypes defined on the surfaces of parts to create the appropriate welds. [More info](https://developer.roblox.com/en-us/api-reference/function/BasePart/MakeJoints)
Material: Specifies the look and feel the Part should have. Note: this does not define the color the Part is, see BrickColor for that. [More info](https://developer.roblox.com/en-us/api-reference/property/BasePart/Material)
NameOcclusion: Sets how to display other humanoid names to this humanoid's player. [More info](https://developer.roblox.com/en-us/api-reference/property/Humanoid/NameOcclusion)
Position: A UDim2 value describing the position of the top-left corner of the GuiObject on screen. More information on UDim2 is available [here](https://developer.roblox.com/en-us/api-reference/datatype/UDim2).
ProcessReceipt:
Callback that is executed for pending Developer Product receipts.

If this function does not return Enum.ProductPurchaseDecision.PurchaseGranted, then you will not be granted the money for the purchase!

The callback will be invoked with a table, containing the following informational fields:

    * PlayerId: int64 -- the id of the player making the purchase.

    * PlaceIdWherePurchased: int64 -- the specific place where the purchase was made.

    * PurchaseId: string -- a unique identifier for the purchase, should be used to prevent granting an item multiple times for one purchase.

    * ProductId: int64 -- the id of the purchased product.

    * CurrencyType: Enum.CurrencyType -- the type of currency used.

    * CurrencySpent: int -- the amount of currency spent on the product for this purchase.
Size: A UDim2 value describing the size of the GuiObject on screen in both absolute and relative coordinates. More information on UDim2 is available [here](https://developer.roblox.com/en-us/api-reference/datatype/UDim2).
SizeConstraint: The direction(s) that an object can be resized in. [More info](https://developer.roblox.com/en-us/api-reference/property/GuiObject/SizeConstraint).
Style: Determines how a button will look, including mouse event states. Uses Enum.ButtonStyle. [More info](https://developer.roblox.com/en-us/api-reference/enum/ButtonStyle)
Team: The Team class is used to represent a faction in a team game. The only valid location for a Team object is under the Teams service. [More info](https://developer.roblox.com/en-us/api-reference/class/Team)
Teams: This Service-level object is the container for all Team objects in a level. A map that supports team games must have a Teams service. [More info](https://developer.roblox.com/en-us/api-reference/class/Team)
TweenPosition: Smoothly moves a GuiObject from its current position to 'endPosition'. The only required argument is 'endPosition'. [More info](https://developer.roblox.com/en-us/api-reference/function/GuiObject/TweenPosition)
TweenSize: Smoothly translates a GuiObject's current size to 'endSize'. The only required argument is 'endSize'. [More info](https://developer.roblox.com/en-us/api-reference/function/GuiObject/TweenSize)
TweenSizeAndPosition: Smoothly translates a GuiObject's current size to 'endSize', and also smoothly translates the GuiObject's current position to 'endPosition'. The only required arguments are 'endSize' and 'endPosition'. [More info](https://developer.roblox.com/en-us/api-reference/function/GuiObject/TweenSizeAndPosition)
WaitForDataReady: Yields until the persistent data for this Player is ready to be loaded. [Info on Data Persistence](http://wiki.roblox.com/index.php/ROBLOX_Scripting_How_To:_Data_Persistence).
